public void testSqlSingleDateWhereFilter() {
    calciteAssert()
        .query("SELECT dateValue\n"
            + "FROM geode.allDataTypesRegion\n"
            + "WHERE dateValue = DATE '2018-02-03'")
        .returnsCount(1)
        .queryContains(
            GeodeAssertions.query("SELECT dateValue AS dateValue "
                + "FROM /allDataTypesRegion "
                + "WHERE dateValue = DATE '2018-02-03'"));

    calciteAssert()
        .query("SELECT dateValue\n"
            + "FROM geode.allDataTypesRegion\n"
            + "WHERE dateValue > DATE '2018-02-03'")
        .returnsCount(2)
        .queryContains(
            GeodeAssertions.query("SELECT dateValue AS dateValue "
                + "FROM /allDataTypesRegion "
                + "WHERE dateValue > DATE '2018-02-03'"));

    calciteAssert()
        .query("SELECT dateValue\n"
            + "FROM geode.allDataTypesRegion\n"
            + "WHERE dateValue < DATE '2018-02-03'")
        .returnsCount(0)
        .queryContains(
            GeodeAssertions.query("SELECT dateValue AS dateValue "
                + "FROM /allDataTypesRegion "
                + "WHERE dateValue < DATE '2018-02-03'"));
  }

commitMessage:
@@@[CALCITE-3892] Make junit test classes and methods non-public where possible

Prior to junit 5.  classes and methods had to be public. This is no
longer the case.

Some classes need to remain public because they are referenced from
elsewhere.  or if they use reflection somehow. The remaining 'public'
keyword will be informative to maintainers.
